{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":2963,"text":"It's said that to be a poet"},{"time":6948,"text":"you have to go to hell and back."}]},{"cues":[{"time":12173,"text":"The first time I visited the prison,"},{"time":15349,"text":"I was not surprised by the noise\nof the padlocks,"},{"time":20025,"text":"or the closing doors,\nor the cell bars,"},{"time":24243,"text":"or by any of the things\nI had imagined."}]},{"cues":[{"time":28246,"text":"Maybe because the prison\nis in a quite open space."},{"time":33559,"text":"You can see the sky."},{"time":35689,"text":"Seagulls fly overhead,\nand you feel like you're next to the sea,"},{"time":39332,"text":"that you're really close to the beach."},{"time":42375,"text":"But in fact, the gulls are looking\nfor food in the dump near the prison."}]},{"cues":[{"time":49250,"text":"I went farther inside and I suddenly saw\ninmates moving across the corridors."},{"time":55886,"text":"Then it was as if I stepped back\nand thought"},{"time":59966,"text":"that I could have very well been\none of them."},{"time":63775,"text":"If I had another story,\nanother context, different luck."},{"time":70457,"text":"Because nobody - nobody -\ncan choose where they're born."}]},{"cues":[{"time":77790,"text":"In 2009, I was invited to join a project"},{"time":82453,"text":"that San Martín National University\nconducted at the Unit 48 penitentiary,"},{"time":87865,"text":"to coordinate a writing workshop."},{"time":91080,"text":"The prison service ceded some land\nat the end of the prison,"},{"time":97525,"text":"which is where they constructed\nthe University Center building."}]},{"cues":[{"time":104152,"text":"The first time I met with the prisoners,"},{"time":106570,"text":"I asked them why they were asking\nfor a writing workshop"},{"time":110245,"text":"and they told me they wanted \nto put on paper"},{"time":113896,"text":"all that they couldn't say and do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":119062,"text":"Right then I decided that I wanted poetry\nto enter the prison."},{"time":125434,"text":"So I said to them\nwhy don't we work with poetry,"},{"time":129044,"text":"if they knew what poetry was."},{"time":131375,"text":"But nobody had a clue\nwhat poetry really was."},{"time":138622,"text":"They also suggested to me"},{"time":140256,"text":"that the workshop should be\nnot just for the inmates"},{"time":142775,"text":"taking university classes, \nbut for all the inmates."},{"time":148641,"text":"And so I said\nthat to start this workshop,"},{"time":151808,"text":"I needed to find a tool\nthat we all had in common."},{"time":155650,"text":"That tool was language."}]},{"cues":[{"time":158756,"text":"We had language, we had the workshop.\nWe could have poetry."},{"time":164948,"text":"But what I hadn't considered\nwas that inequality exists in prison, too."},{"time":170774,"text":"Many of the prisoners hadn't even\ncompleted grammar school."},{"time":175895,"text":"Many couldn't use cursive,\ncould barely print."},{"time":183410,"text":"They didn't write fluently, either."},{"time":187082,"text":"So we started looking for short poems."},{"time":191693,"text":"Very short, but very powerful."}]},{"cues":[{"time":194759,"text":"And we started to read, and we'd read\none author, then another author,"},{"time":198507,"text":"and by reading such short poems,\nthey all began to realize"},{"time":203982,"text":"that what the poetic language did\nwas to break a certain logic,"},{"time":208639,"text":"and create another system."},{"time":210394,"text":"Breaking the logic of language\nalso breaks the logic of the system"},{"time":213988,"text":"under which they've learned to respond."},{"time":218550,"text":"So a new system appeared,"},{"time":222043,"text":"new rules that made them\nunderstand very quickly,"},{"time":227202,"text":"- very quickly -"},{"time":229081,"text":"that with poetic language"},{"time":231230,"text":"they would be able to say\nabsolutely whatever they wanted."}]},{"cues":[{"time":239479,"text":"It's said that to be a poet\nyou have to go to hell and back."},{"time":245475,"text":"And they have plenty of hell.\nPlenty of hell."}]},{"cues":[{"time":249974,"text":"One of them once said:\n\"In prison you never sleep."},{"time":254589,"text":"You can never sleep in jail.\nYou can never close your eyelids.\""},{"time":260351,"text":"And so, like I’m doing now,\nI gave them a moment of silence,"},{"time":266707,"text":"then said,\n“That's what poetry is, you guys."},{"time":272309,"text":"It's in this prison universe\nthat you have all around you."},{"time":277494,"text":"Everything you say\nabout how you never sleep,"},{"time":279774,"text":"it exudes fear."},{"time":281464,"text":"All the things that go unwritten --\nall of that is poetry.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":287469,"text":"So we started appropriating that hell;"},{"time":291676,"text":"we plunged ourselves, headfirst,\ninto the seventh circle."},{"time":295184,"text":"And in that seventh circle of hell,\nour very own, beloved circle,"},{"time":299222,"text":"they learned that they could\nmake the walls invisible,"},{"time":303434,"text":"that they could make the windows yell,"},{"time":305604,"text":"and that we could hide inside the shadows."},{"time":311504,"text":"When the first year\nof the workshop had ended,"},{"time":315464,"text":"we organized a little closing party,"},{"time":317872,"text":"like you do when a job is done\nwith so much love,"},{"time":321562,"text":"and you want to celebrate with a party."}]},{"cues":[{"time":324512,"text":"We called family, friends, \nthe university authorities."},{"time":328979,"text":"The only thing the inmates\nhad to do was read a poem,"},{"time":333321,"text":"and receive their diplomas and applause."},{"time":335558,"text":"That was our simple party."},{"time":340105,"text":"The only thing I want to leave you with"},{"time":346694,"text":"is the moment in which those men,"},{"time":351019,"text":"some of them just huge\nwhen standing next to me,"},{"time":353519,"text":"or the young boys - so young,\nbut with an enormous pride,"},{"time":359230,"text":"held their papers and trembled\nlike little kids and sweated,"},{"time":365078,"text":"and read their poems with their\nvoices completely broken."}]},{"cues":[{"time":372042,"text":"That moment made me think a lot"},{"time":376959,"text":"that for most of them,\nit was surely the very first time"},{"time":381066,"text":"that someone applauded them\nfor something they had done."},{"time":388809,"text":"In prison there are things\nthat can't be done."},{"time":392262,"text":"In prison, you can't dream.\nIn prison, you can't cry."},{"time":397118,"text":"There are words that are virtually\nforbidden, like the word \"time,\""},{"time":402147,"text":"the word \"future,\" the word \"wish\"."},{"time":407016,"text":"But we dared to dream, and to dream a lot."},{"time":412322,"text":"We decided\nthat they were going to write a book."},{"time":417126,"text":"Not only did they write a book,\nbut they also bound it themselves."},{"time":421546,"text":"That was at the end of 2010."},{"time":424642,"text":"Then, we doubled the bet\nand wrote another book."},{"time":429051,"text":"And we bound that one, too."},{"time":430685,"text":"That was a short time ago,\nat the end of last year."},{"time":436474,"text":"What I see week after week,"},{"time":440000,"text":"is how they're turning\ninto different people;"},{"time":444357,"text":"how they're being transformed."},{"time":446904,"text":"How words are empowering them\nwith a dignity they had never known,"},{"time":451251,"text":"that they couldn't even imagine."},{"time":453334,"text":"They had no idea such dignity\ncould come from them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":459130,"text":"At the workshop, in that beloved hell\nwe share, we all give something."},{"time":466397,"text":"We open our hands and hearts and give\nwhat we have, what we can."},{"time":470997,"text":"All of us;\nall of us equally."},{"time":473151,"text":"And so you feel that at least\nin a small way"},{"time":477766,"text":"you're repairing\nthat huge social fracture"},{"time":481416,"text":"which makes it so that for many of them,"},{"time":486634,"text":"prison is their only destination."},{"time":492172,"text":"I remember a verse\nby a tremendous poet, a great poet,"},{"time":498586,"text":"from our Unit 48 workshop,\nNicolás Dorado:"},{"time":508395,"text":"\"I will need an infinite thread\nto sew up this huge wound.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":515485,"text":"Poetry does that; it sews up\nthe wounds of exclusion."},{"time":521004,"text":"It opens doors. \nPoetry works as a mirror."},{"time":526417,"text":"It creates a mirror, which is the poem."},{"time":529762,"text":"They recognize themselves,\nthey look at themselves in the poem"},{"time":533745,"text":"and write from who they are,\nand are from what they write."}]},{"cues":[{"time":538808,"text":"In order to write,"},{"time":541513,"text":"they need to appropriate\nthe moment of writing"},{"time":545704,"text":"which is a moment\nof extraordinary freedom."},{"time":549155,"text":"They have to get into their heads,\nsearch for that bit of freedom"},{"time":552098,"text":"that can never be taken away\nwhen they write"},{"time":557124,"text":"and that is also useful\nto realize that freedom is possible"},{"time":560635,"text":"even inside a prison,"},{"time":562973,"text":"and that the only bars we have\nin our wonderful space"},{"time":568235,"text":"is the word \"bars,\""},{"time":570097,"text":"and that all of us in our hell\nburn with happiness"},{"time":573959,"text":"when we light the wick of the word."}]},{"cues":[{"time":577669,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":605143,"text":"I told you a lot about the prison,\na lot about what I experience"},{"time":611597,"text":"every week, and how I enjoy it\nand transform myself with the inmates."},{"time":616178,"text":"But you don't know how much I'd like it"},{"time":619593,"text":"if you could feel, live, experience,\neven for a few seconds,"},{"time":625159,"text":"what I enjoy every week\nand what makes me who I am."},{"time":632151,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":641228,"text":"Martín Bustamante: \nThe heart chews tears of time;"},{"time":645464,"text":"blinded by that light,"},{"time":648346,"text":"it hides the speed of existence"},{"time":651721,"text":"where the images go rowing by."},{"time":653874,"text":"It fights; it hangs on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":656847,"text":"The heart cracks under sad gazes,"},{"time":660554,"text":"rides on storms that spread fire,"},{"time":664327,"text":"lifts chests lowered by shame,"},{"time":667451,"text":"knows that it's not just reading\nand going on,"},{"time":670627,"text":"it also wishes to see the infinite blue."}]},{"cues":[{"time":674457,"text":"The heart sits down to think about things,"},{"time":678185,"text":"fights to avoid being ordinary,"},{"time":680897,"text":"tries to love without hurting,"},{"time":684320,"text":"breathes the sun,\ngiving courage to itself,"},{"time":688023,"text":"surrenders, travels toward reason."}]},{"cues":[{"time":692391,"text":"The heart fights among the swamps,"},{"time":695294,"text":"skirts the edge of the underworld,"},{"time":698819,"text":"falls exhausted, but won't give in\nto what's easy,"},{"time":703101,"text":"while irregular steps of intoxication"},{"time":705590,"text":"wake up,"},{"time":707167,"text":"wake the stillness."}]},{"cues":[{"time":709057,"text":"I'm Martín Bustamante,"},{"time":711756,"text":"I'm a prisoner in Unit 48 of San Martín,"},{"time":715254,"text":"today is my day of temporary release."},{"time":718112,"text":"And for me, poetry and literature\nhave changed my life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":721784,"text":"Thank you very much!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":722905,"text":"Cristina Domenech: Thank you!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":724325,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}